The area

Neighborhood: Belém
Belém is the "capital of the Portuguese Discoveries" and a photographer's paradise. You can spend an entire day exploring this neighborhood: monuments (Jerónimos Monastery, Belém Tower, Monument to the Discoveries), museums (Coach Museum, Centro Cultural de Belém) and breathtaking views of the Tagus river will make your visit worth your time. Belém also offers a variety of restaurants and cafes, namely the famous - and delicious - "Pastéis de Belém" (typical Portuguese custard tarts; make sure you buy an extra box of those!). Easily accessible from Lisbon's historic center, Belém is a must-do, especially if you're spending more than one day visiting the Portuguese capital.

Attractive park between Jerónimos Monastery and the Discoveries Monument
Apr 2023
Jardim da Praca do Imperio is a 3.3 hectare garden located in between Jerónimos Monastery and the Monument to the Discoveries in Belem. It was opened to the public in 1940 as part of the Great Exhibition of the Portuguese World event.

You will find nicely landscaped grounds and park benches along with a large centre fountain surrounded Portuguese style cobblestone images of 32 floral coats of arms representing the capitals of Portuguese districts, archipelagos and former colonies. There is a large scale cobblestone patter of the Portuguese Shield flanked by two Horses Ponds on the southern side of the park along Ave. da India.

The garden is fairly attractive and a nice place to grab a seat and rest your feet a bit while sightseeing around Belem. Unfortunately, many are briskly making their way between the Monastery, Discoveries Monument and Belem Tower further to the West and pass right through with little time to enjoy the park.
Written June 6, 2023

Nice, small, formal gardens
Mar 2023 • Couples
This garden makes for a pleasant stroll between Belem’s big hitting attractions. There is a fascinating little corner, easily missed, where 25 plant species found in the monastery carvings and artwork are being grown, with explanation boards. The garden is well maintained and the central fountain and large pond at the main road side are both very nice.
